    stable 1.5 1.4.2
   require db e2fsprogs ncurses readline zlib

  optional Linux-PAM    --with-pam    --without-pam    for pluggable authentication
  optional heimdal      --with-krb5   --without-krb5   for heimdal kerberos 5 support
  optional openssl      ''            ''               for secure socket connect support
  optional shishi       --with-shishi --without-shishi for shishi kerberos 5 support
  optional tcp_wrappers --with-wrap   --without-wrap   for tcp wrapper support
  optional xinetd       ''            ''               for launching servers upon demand

  switch '' --disable-ftp     Compile and install ftp
  switch '' --disable-ping    Compile and install ping
  switch '' --disable-ping6   Compile and install ping6
  switch '' --disable-rcp     Compile and install rcp
  switch '' --disable-rlogin  Compile and install rlogin
  switch '' --disable-rsh     Compile and install rsh
  switch '' --disable-talk    Compile and install talk
  switch '' --disable-telnet  Compile and install telnet
  switch '' --disable-tftp    Compile and install tftp
  switch '' --disable-ftpd    Compile and install ftpd
  switch '' --disable-inetd   Compile and install inetd
  switch '' --disable-rexecd  Compile and install rexecd
  switch '' --disable-rlogind Compile and install rlogind
  switch '' --disable-rshd    Compile and install rshd
  switch '' --disable-talkd   Compile and install talkd
  switch '' --disable-telnetd Compile and install telnetd
  switch '' --disable-tftpd   Compile and install tftpd
  switch '' --disable-uucpd   Compile and install uucpd

    ignore 'shishi'
  category network/chat network/ftp
 attribute client console server
       url $GNU_URL
    source inetutils/inetutils-$VERSION.tar.gz
  homepage http://www.gnu.org/software/inetutils/inetutils.html
      opts --disable-syslogd --disable-ifconfig --disable-whois --disable-logger
# should ifconfig whois and/or syslogd from inetutils be supported?
  estimate 1200
      desc 'inetutils contains the netkit networking tools.
Clients: ftp ping rpc rlogin rsh talk telnet tftp
Servers: ftpd inetd rexecd rlogind rshd talkd telnetd tftpd uucpd

The ftp, ping, telent, and tftp clients may be useful occasionally.
The servers are definitely not worth using unless you live in a
country that prevents use of ssh/sshd strong encryption methods
for secure logins.

Unlike netkit-combo this spell does not invoke
any of the servers automatically from xinetd.
SA would likely run any of these servers
within a chrooted or caged file system
rather than allowing full access to the box.'
